---
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const pageTitle = 'Best Budget Mechanical Keyboard for Work 2026';
const pageDescription = 'Honest review of the Keychron K2 wireless mechanical keyboard. Compact 75% layout, hot-swappable, and dual Mac/Windows compatibility under $80.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} />
    <style>
      main { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: #333; }
      h1 { color: #232f3e; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
      .meta { color: #666; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
      .product-box { background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
      .product-box h2 { margin-top: 0; }
      .product-box ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; }
      .btn { display: inline-block; background: #ff9900; color: #000; padding: 12px 24px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
      .btn:hover { background: #e68a00; }
      .disclaimer { font-size: 0.8rem; color: #888; margin-top: 3rem; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 1rem; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Best Budget Mechanical Keyboard for Work</h1>
      <div class="meta">Updated May 2026 · Under $80</div>

      <p>If you type 8+ hours a day, a mechanical keyboard is one of the best investments for your wrists and productivity. After testing multiple budget options, one 75% wireless board stands out for its Mac/Windows dual compatibility and hot-swap switches.</p>

      <div class="product-box">
        <h2>🏆 Keychron K2 (Hot-Swappable)</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>75% compact layout</strong> — keeps arrow keys and function row, saves desk space</li>
          <li><strong>Wireless & Wired</strong> — Bluetooth 5.1 for 3 devices, USB-C wired mode</li>
          <li><strong>Mac & Windows</strong> — keycaps for both, physical switch on the side</li>
          <li><strong>Hot-swappable</strong> — change switches without soldering</li>
          <li><strong>4000 mAh battery</strong> — up to 72 hours wireless use</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/s?k=keychron+k2&tag=toolwise20-20" class="btn" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored">Check Current Price on Amazon</a>
      </div>

      <h3>Why it wins at this price</h3>
      <p>Most sub-$100 mechanical keyboards force you to choose between Mac compatibility and wireless. The Keychron K2 gives you both, plus a layout that does not require a learning curve like 60% boards. The Gateron switches are smooth, and the frame has enough weight that it does not slide around on the desk.</p>

      <h3>Who should buy it</h3>
      <p>Remote workers, developers, and anyone who wants a premium typing feel without spending $150+ on a custom board. It is not the quietest keyboard, but for private offices and home desks, the tactile feedback is worth it.</p>

      <div class="disclaimer">
        Disclosure: As an Amazon Associate I earn from qualifying purchases. This review is based on independent research and reader feedback.
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>